<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Beef Barbacoa
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 11 hours
TOTAL TIME: 11 hours 15 minutes
COURSE: Main Course
CUISINE: American, Mexican
KEYWORD: beef, crock pot
SERVINGS: 10 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="1.0 Teaspoon">Pepper</ingredient><ingredient amount="2.0 Tablespoon">Olive Oil</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0 Pound">Beef</ingredient><ingredient amount="3.0">Garlic</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
In a small bowl, stir together salt, rosemary, pepper, coriander, and chile powder. 
Rub spice mixture on both sides of roast. Set aside.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add roast and brown on both sides. 
Place roast in slow cooker. 
Add water, bay leaves, and garlic to slow cooker. 
Cover, and cook on low for 10 hours or on high for 5 hours. 
Stir in barbecue sauce and hot sauce. 
Continue cooking for another hour on low. 
Shred beef in sauce. 
</instructions>
<cuisine>American, Mexican</cuisine></recipe>